{"lemma":"مُعَيَّنٌ","slug":"مُعَيَّنٌ","root":"ع.#.ن","root_slug":"ع-_-ن","root_link":"/words/roots/ع-_-ن","pos":"ADJ","pos_camel":"adj","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"مُعَيَّنٌ","root":"عين","pos":"N","occurrence_count":4},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":5,"pos_tags":["adj","noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":7},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n31302"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%85%D9%8F%D8%B9%D9%8E%D9%8A%D9%8E%D9%91%D9%86%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"well, spring, water source","tags":["archaic"],"examples":[{"text":"يَطُوفُ عَلَيْهِمْ وِلْدَانٌ مُّخَلَّدُونَ بِأَكْوَابٍ وَأَبَارِيقَ وَكَأْسٍ مِّن مَّعِينٍ","english":"There will circulate among them young boys made eternal, with beakers, pitchers and a glass of spring water."}]},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"active participle of عَيَّنَ (ʕayyana).","tags":["active","archaic","form-of","participle"]},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"passive participle of عَيَّنَ (ʕayyana)","tags":["archaic","form-of","participle","passive"]},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"definite, clear, determined, known","tags":["archaic"]},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"rhombic","tags":["archaic"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"rhombus","tags":["archaic"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"the state of Maʿīn in ancient Yemen","tags":["archaic"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Cognate with Hebrew מַעְיָן (ma'ayán, “spring, fountain”).\n\nDerived from the active participle and passive participle of عَيَّنَ (ʕayyana).\n\nFrom Old South Arabian 𐩣𐩲𐩬 (mʿn)."},"ipa":["/ma.ʕiːn/","/mu.ʕaj.jin/","/mu.ʕaj.jan/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n31302","headword_ar":"مُعَيَّنٌ","root":"Eyn","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  A garment"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"figured with eyes"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"brj","text_ar":"برج"},{"kind":"text","text":":) or a garment"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the figuring of which are small"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taraAbiyE","text_ar":"تَرَابِيع"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app. meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"quadrangular forms"},{"kind":"text","text":"(in the CK"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tarobiyE","text_ar":"تَرْبِيع"},{"kind":"text","text":")]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"like the eyes of wild animals."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) ―         -b2-  And (assumed tropical:)  A bull"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having a blackness between his eyes:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a bull;"},{"kind":"text","text":"so called because of the largeness of his eyes: or so called because"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having spots of black and white, as though there were eyes upon his skin."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ham p. 293.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"page_break","n":2219},{"kind":"text","text":"And (assumed tropical:)  Locusts ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaraAd","text_ar":"جَرَاد"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which, when stripped of the integument, are seen to be white and red:"},{"kind":"text","text":"mentioned by Az in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ynE","text_ar":"ينع"},{"kind":"text","text":", on the authority of ISh. (TA.)       -A2-  [Also, as pass. part. n. of 2, (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Individuated,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"particularized;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"distinguished from the generality,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"aggregate:"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.: see the verb. Hence]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"niy~apN muEay~anapN","text_ar":"نِيَّةٌ مُعَيَّنَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A distinct, particular,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"special, purpose;"},{"kind":"text","text":"lit.]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a purpose made distinct:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and it is allowable for one to attribute the action to the purpose, tropically; and thus to say ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"niy~apN muEay~inapN","text_ar":"نِيَّةٌ مُعَيِّنَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A distinguishing purpose"},{"kind":"text","text":"], using the act. part. n. (Msb.)"}],"source_refs":["K"]}]},"classical_definitions":{"source":"hawramani","url":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/%D9%85%D8%B9%D9%8A%D9%86/","headword_ar":"معين","entries":[{"lexicon_id":"dictionary_32","lexicon_en":"Supplément aux dictionnaires arabes by Reinhart Dozy (d. 1883 CE)","lexicon_ar":"تكملة المعاجم العربية لرينهارت دوزي","permalink":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/?p=53812#8f6ea8","body_html":"معين: معين (مشتقة من عين)، فتن، سحر، خلب، بهر العيون، رقي (الكالا- aojar أي عان، أصاب بالعين أو اللامة).<br>تمعين: السحر بالنظر (الكالا - aojadora) ."}]}}